gle</span><hr size=1> First of all, I have not called anyone &quot;stupid&quot; or their comments or opinion &quot;ridiculous&quot;.  Trying to make an argument stronger by ridiculing the opposing position is a tactic that just makes you look childish.<br>
<br>
I made up no numbers, I made an estimate, and I still think that estimate is sound.<br>
<br>
You say PST was chosen because Verant is there, so?<br>
<br>
You say there was an informal poll that said most wanted it on PST.  I have been on Brell since the beginning, I remember no such poll.  Perhaps if we want to see general reaction, we should set up a poll now.<br>
<br>
I said in my post that I don't care what the population split is between east coast and west coast.  I don't care if 90% of the Brell population is west coast.  Having to post intentions at 3am is just crazy.  If you move it to midnight eastern time then the west coast people can post at 9pm, neither of those times is all that bad.  If you want to be nice to the Europeans, then make it Noon eastern.  It really does not matter to me, but having to post raid intentions between 1am and 7am is extremely tough on those of us that have jobs and are getting older, and there is no good reason for it.<br>
<br>
Yes, every so often someone comes and bitches about it, I have bitched about it before.  And, I will continue to bitch about it every time I have to stay up till 3am to post an intention.  Oh, and guess what, sometimes people bitching about something long and hard enough does initiate change.<br>
<br>
Oakendar Silverwulf<br>
Preserver of the Glade<br>
