<br>
Hey I gotta call a duck a duck. <br>
<br>
And when you use words like &quot;majority&quot; and &quot;1/4&quot; as estimates, you are making up a number. Estimates are an educated guess based on factual but incomplete information. (Webster's definition, not mine). If you make those numbers up with no factual basis (As you freely admit) then you are making up numbers. I stand by my post on the subject, and by my opinion on the silliness of this argument, especially as it relates to a dying and absurd reservation system. <br>
<br>
